Title : First office application
Text : In [[telecommunication]], '''First Office Application''' (FOA) is a phase in [[New product development|development]] of new equipment or [[technology]]. The FOA phase is the first deployment (pilot) of the equipment or technology in an actual customer environment after internal test and acceptance phases are completed.<ref>{{cite journal|title=The 5ESS Switching System: System Test, First‚ÄêOffice Application, and Early Field Experience - Bauer - 1985 - AT&T Technical Journal - Wiley Online Library |doi=10.1002/j.1538-7305.1985.tb00284.x }}</ref>

